ing it with raw XP setting.\n-\n-## Why\n-\n-Direct XP manipulation (`GOD MODE: Set xp to 300`) skips the natural level-up detection path. The narrative approach lets the LLM compute XP naturally, which tests the actual code paths users trigger.\n-\n-## Applies To\n-\n-- `testing_mcp/` E2E tests using MCPTestBase\n-- Any test that needs to trigger level-up rewards flow\n...\n</persisted-output>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47505249-54d8-47bd-9057-90c6dad053a3","uuid":"9ae84acb-7a22-49c8-b8c1-915d8b4b8f74","timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:44:27.996Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"diff --git a/.beads/BD-W2-7m1.md b/.beads/BD-W2-7m1.md\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex 365ea89131..0000000000\n--- a/.beads/BD-W2-7m1.md\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,28 +0,0 @@\n----\n-id: W2-7m1\n-title: world_events split storage bug causes stale pending events\n-status: open\n-priority: high\n----\n-\n-## The Bug\n-\n-world_events stored in BOTH Firestore locations:\n-1. `game_state.world_events` (top-level)\n-2. `custom_campaign_state.world_events` (nested)\n-\n-Extraction function copies nested to top but does NOT delete from nested location.\n-\n-## Evidence\n-\n-- 46 campaigns affected\n-- turn_generated mismatch: top=47, nested=None\n-- Campaign: `00h8j6i2KoYcngsvjqro`\n-\n-## Test\n-\n-`testing_mcp/test_world_events_split_bug.py` - RED (split exists) vs GREEN (fixed)\n-\n-## Fix Required\n-\n-Add DELETE step after extracting nested world_events to top-level.\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/.beads/BD-godmode-leveling.md b/.beads/BD-godmode-leveling.md\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex 2fc695d3eb..0000000000\n--- a/.beads/BD-godmode-leveling.md\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,24 +0,0 @@\n-# BD-godmode-leveling: God Mode Narrative XP for E2E Tests\n-\n-**Status**: OPEN\n-**Created**: 2026-04-13\n-**Context**: Level/XP centralization (PR #6233)\n-\n-## Learning\n-\n-For E2E level-up tests, use narrative god mode instructions rather than directly setting XP values:\n-